  "prompt": "Why did Vice President Joe Biden say \"God save the Queen\" at the end of the joint session to confirm the election of President Trump?",
  "response": "Joe Biden's remark \"God save the Queen\" at the end of the joint session to confirm the election of President Trump on January 6, 2017, was likely a lighthearted or humorous comment rather than a serious or intentional statement. Biden, known for his folksy and sometimes off-the-cuff remarks, may have been using the phrase as a non sequitur or as a way to bring levity to the proceedings. There was no official explanation for why he chose those exact words, but it was generally understood not to carry political significance.",
